      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:129:1",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ سُوءَ الْخُلُقِ لَيُفْسِدُ الْعَمَلَ كَمَا يُفْسِدُ الْخَلُّ الْعَسَلَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The evil mannerism is a spoiler of the deed just as the vinegar spoils the honey’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, ‘Wickedness and evil behavior destroys and spoils good deeds just as vinegar spoils honey.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
